13/12/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The government officially asked parliament on Wednesday (December 12th) to extend the country's military presence in Iraq for another year. 
A contingent of 155 Bulgarian troops is responsible for protecting the Ashraf refugee camp. 
Their mandate expires on March 31st 2008, and parliament must approve any additional mandate. 
(Sega, Klasa - 13/12/07; BTA, Actualno - 12/12/07)
